						<summary>

						<p>On the base of a pillar in the enclosure of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śivappa Nāyaka 1685 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It speaks of a worship rendered by Siddammāji daughter of Keḷadi Śivappa-nāyaka and his wife Lingammāji, to the god Kaṁbada-Vinayakadēva of Śrīṅgapura (Śringēri).</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1606, Raktakshi, Māgha ba. 12, Friday corresponding to 1685 A.D., February, 20.</p>						

						</summary>
